@BeginModule
@NewPage
@Name      = Select
@Title     = Select fields
@Section   = Selection
@Class     = Selection
@Arguments = ifile ofile
@Operators = selcode delcode selvar delvar sellevel selgrid selgridname selzaxis selzaxisname seltabnum selrec

@BeginDescription
This module selects some fields from @file{ifile} and write the result to @file{ofile}.
Which fields are selected depends on the actual operator name and the parameters.
@EndDescription
@EndModule


@BeginOperator_selcode
@Title     = Select codes
@Parameter = codes

@BeginDescription
Selects all fields with a code number in a user given list.
@EndDescription
@EndOperator


@BeginOperator_delcode
@Title     = Delete codes
@Parameter = codes

@BeginDescription
Deletes all fields with a code number in a user given list.
@EndDescription
@EndOperator


@BeginOperator_selvar
@Title     = Select variables
@Parameter = vars

@BeginDescription
Selects all fields with a variable name in a user given list.
@EndDescription
@EndOperator


@BeginOperator_delvar
@Title     = Delete variables
@Parameter = vars

@BeginDescription
Deletes all fields with a variable name in a user given list.
@EndDescription
@EndOperator


@BeginOperator_sellevel
@Title     = Select levels
@Parameter = levels

@BeginDescription
Selects all fields with a level in a user given list.
@EndDescription
@EndOperator


@BeginOperator_selgrid
@Title     = Select grids
@Parameter = grids

@BeginDescription
Selects all fields with a grid in a user given list.
@EndDescription
@EndOperator


@BeginOperator_selgridname
@Title     = Select grid by name
@Parameter = gridnames

@BeginDescription
Selects all fields with a grid name in a user given list.
@EndDescription
@EndOperator


@BeginOperator_selzaxis
@Title     = Select zaxis
@Parameter = zaxis

@BeginDescription
Selects all fields with a zaxis in a user given list.
@EndDescription
@EndOperator


@BeginOperator_selzaxisname
@Title     = Select zaxis by name
@Parameter = zaxisnames

@BeginDescription
Selects all fields with a zaxis name in a user given list.
@EndDescription
@EndOperator


@BeginOperator_seltabnum
@Title     = Select parameter table number
@Parameter = tabnum

@BeginDescription
Selects all fields with a parameter table number in a user given list.
@EndDescription
@EndOperator


@BeginOperator_selrec
@Title     = Select records
@Parameter = records

@BeginDescription
Selects all fields with a record number in a user given list.
This operator does not work on netCDF data!
@EndDescription
@EndOperator


@BeginParameter
@Item = codes
INTEGER  Comma separated list of code numbers
@Item = vars
STRING   Comma separated list of variable names
@Item = levels
FLOAT    Comma separated list of levels
@Item = grids
INTEGER  Comma separated list of grid numbers
@Item = gridnames
STRING   Comma separated list of grid names
@Item = zaxis
INTEGER  Comma separated list of zaxis numbers
@Item = zaxisnames
STRING   Comma separated list of zaxis names
@Item = tabnum
INTEGER  Comma separated list of parameter table numbers
@Item = records
INTEGER  Comma separated list of records
@EndParameter


@BeginExample
Assumed the input dataset has 3 variables with the code number 129, 130 and 139.
To select the variables with the code number 129 and 139 use:
@BeginVerbatim
   cdo selcode,129,139 ifile ofile
@EndVerbatim
You can also select the code number 129 and 139 by deleting the code number 130 with:
@BeginVerbatim
   cdo delcode,130 ifile ofile
@EndVerbatim
@EndExample
